ose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def tripletCount(self, a: List[int], b: List[int], c: List[int]) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "To solve the problem, we need to count the number of triplets (a[i], b[j], c[k]) such that the bitwise XOR of the elements of each triplet has an even number of set bits. \n\nThe key observation here is that the XOR of three numbers will have an even number of set bits if and only if the number of 1s in the binary representation of the XOR result is even. This can be achieved in the following scenarios:\n1. All three numbers have an even number of set bits.\n2. One number has an even number of set bits, and two numbers have an odd number of set bits.\n\nWe can count the number of elements in each array that have an even number of set bits and those that have an odd number of set bits. Let's denote:\n- `even_a` as the count of numbers with an even number of set bits in array `a`.\n- `odd_a` as the count of numbers with an odd number of set bits in array `a`.\n- `even_b` and `odd_b` similarly for array `b`.\n- `even_c` and `odd_c` similarly for array `c`.\n\nThe total number of valid triplets can then be calculated as:\n\\[ \\text{total\\_triplets} = (\\text{even\\_a} \\times \\text{even\\_b} \\times \\text{even\\_c}) + (\\text{even\\_a} \\times \\text{odd\\_b} \\times \\text{odd\\_c}) + (\\text{odd\\_a} \\times \\text{even\\_b} \\times \\text{odd\\_c}) + (\\text{odd\\_a} \\times \\text{odd\\_b} \\times \\text{even\\_c}) \\]\n\nLet's implement this in the provided code format:\n\n```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def tripletCount(self, a: List[int], b: List[int], c: List[int]) -> int:\n        def count_even_odd_bits(arr):\n            even_count = 0\n            odd_count = 0\n            for num in arr:\n                if bin(num).count('1') % 2 == 0:\n                    even_count += 1\n                else:\n                    odd_count += 1\n            return even_count, odd_count\n        \n        even_a, odd_a = count_even_odd_bits(a)\n        even_b, odd_b = count_even_odd_bits(b)\n        even_c, odd_c = count_even_odd_bits(c)\n        \n        total_triplets = (even_a * even_b * even_c) + \\\n                         (even_a * odd_b * odd_c) + \\\n                         (odd_a * even_b * odd_c) + \\\n                         (odd_a * odd_b * even_c)\n        \n        return total_triplets\n```\n\nThis code defines a helper function `count_even_odd_bits` to count the numbers with even and odd set bits in a given array. It then calculates the total number of valid triplets using the formula derived above.", "estimated_date": 1719100800000}